February 18, 1946 was a Monday and it was the 49th day of the year 1946 in the Gregorian calendar.

February 18, 1946 can also be written as 2/18/1946 in the US and as 18/2/1946 in UK and Europe.

Moon phase

The moon phase on February 18, 1946 was Full Moon.

The moon phase refers to the appearance of the Moon in the night sky on February 18, 1946 and is determined by the portion of the Moon's illuminated surface that is visible from Earth.

An observer located in New York City on February 18, 1946 at 10pm, would see the moon, being 88% full, rising at 08:14 pm and setting at 08:47 am.

The previous full moon was on Feb 16, 1946 while the next full moon would come on Mar 17, 1946.

What is special about February 18th?

February 18th refers to a specific date on the calendar, which is the 18th day of the month of February. It is a date that occurs annually and is part of the Gregorian calendar, which is widely used around the world.
